Tony ALEXANDER, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 6965. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit Oct. 13, 1933. Tony Alexander, in pro. per. H. T. Nichols, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and..HUTCHESON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On the authority of United States v. Barnow, 239 U. S. 74, 36 S. Ct. 19, 60 L. Ed. 155, and Lamar v. United States, 241 U. S. 103, 36 S. Ct. 535, 60 L. Ed. 912, the judgment is' affirmed.
